duck: Parametric statistics, a branch of statistics that assumes that the data has come from a type of probability distribution
Parametric model, a family of distributions that can be described using a finite number of parameters
Parametric equation, a representation of a curve through equations, as functions of a variable called parameter

parametric definition: any of a set of equations that express the coordinates of the points of a curve as functions of one parameter or that express the coordinates of the points of a surface as functions of two parameters.
